2. Memory Writes Are Governed Actions

Nothing enters memory by default.

Every write passes explicit gates:

Write Gates
	1.	Provenance â€” source and confidence known
	2.	Utility â€” future reuse potential
	3.	Stability â€” survives stress / flip / critique
	4.	Risk â€” privacy, projection, misuse

If any gate fails, the item is dropped or remains ephemeral.

