5. Memory Integration Modes

Memory participates in reasoning in three explicit ways:

1. Memory-as-Context

Relevant artifacts are retrieved and appended as references.

2. Memory-as-Daemon

A synthesis pass generates a distilled state before reasoning.

3. Memory-as-Gate

Outputs are down-weighted or vetoed if they conflict with invariants.

This integrates cleanly with the Pantheon SDK and Judge protocol.

